{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2013}} The '''Handball Cup of Slovenia''' was first played after [[Slovenia]]n independence in 1991. The most successful clubs are [[RK Celje|Celje]] (men) and [[RK Krim|Krim]] (women).
==History== The Handball Cup of [[Slovenia]] has been played since the Slovenian [[Ten-Day War|independence]], starting with the 1991–92 season.
